{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17639069","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17639069"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:03:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:03:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17759"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17759","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17759"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.31,0.12,0.04,0.54,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10473"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74834"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10473","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10473"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17759"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60340"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"375"},{"type":"tags","id":"1127"},{"type":"tags","id":"1194"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"3310"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"9600"},{"type":"tags","id":"12913"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24445"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24450"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74834","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74834"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 15-year-old male was unintentionally struck to the right side of his head with a hockey stick during a game. He had a brief loss of consciousness and wasn\u0027t brought to seek medical attention as he regained consciousness soon after. Four hours after the game, he was found unconscious at home.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following types of intracranial bleed is most likely to occur in this scenario?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Subdural haematoma","Subarachnoid haemorrhage","Intracerebral haemorrhage","Epidural haematoma","Intraventricular haemorrhage"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis clinical scenario is characteristic of an \u003Cstrong\u003Eepidural haematoma\u003C/strong\u003E, which is often associated with a rupture of the middle meningeal artery following a head injury. The classic presentation includes a brief loss of consciousness, a lucid interval, and then rapid neurological deterioration. The CT scan finding of a biconvex, hyperdense lesion is typical of an epidural haematoma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubdural haematoma\u003C/strong\u003E typically results from tearing of bridging veins and presents with a crescent-shaped lesion on CT. It often occurs in older adults or those with brain atrophy and may have a more insidious onset.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubarachnoid haemorrhage\u003C/strong\u003E is usually due to rupture of a cerebral aneurysm and presents with a sudden, severe headache often described as a \u0027thunderclap\u0027 headache. CT findings include blood in the subarachnoid space.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntracerebral haemorrhage\u003C/strong\u003E involves bleeding within the brain tissue itself and can result from hypertension or trauma. CT findings show a hyperdense area within the brain parenchyma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntraventricular haemorrhage\u003C/strong\u003E involves bleeding into the ventricular system and is often secondary to other types of haemorrhage. It is less commonly associated with trauma and more often seen in premature infants or as a complication of other bleeds.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Rupture of the middle meningeal artery results in an epidural haematoma.","Epidural haematomas are often associated with a lucid interval followed by rapid deterioration.","Prompt surgical intervention is often required to manage epidural haematomas."],"references":["Khairat A, Waseem M. Epidural Hematoma. [Updated 2023 Jul 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK518982/","Zussman BM, Goldschmidt E, Faraji AH, Salvetti DJ, Jankowitz BT. Middle Meningeal Artery Embolization for the Treatment of an Expanding Epidural Hematoma. World Neurosurg. 2019 Aug;128:284-286. doi: 10.1016/j.wneu.2019.05.084. Epub 2019 May 17. PMID: 31108255.","Madison MT, Graupman PC, Carroll JM, Torok CM, Touchette JC, Nussbaum ES. Traumatic epidural hematoma treated with endovascular coil embolization. Surg Neurol Int. 2021 Jul 6;12:322. doi: 10.25259/SNI_939_2020. PMID: 34345463; PMCID: PMC8326102."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60340"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17759"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60340","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60340"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-27T15:15:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T18:57:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10473"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74834"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"t